expéditionnaire (plural expéditionnaires)

  1. expeditionary

expéditionnaire m or f by sense (plural expéditionnaires)

  1. (obsolete) an office worker who makes copies of texts by hand; copyist
  2. a person or company that organizes shipments for individuals or corporations to get goods from the manufacturer or producer to a market, customer or final point of distribution; forwarder, forwarding agent
trans: an office worker who makes copies of texts by hand
